main event: A radar event involving an unidentified object was observed for 9 seconds on June 21, 1956 in Cincinnati, Ohio.
interesting points: The object was initially detected on radar, leading meteorologists to describe the event,The radar analysis concluded that ground clutter was the most likely cause of the signal,Two meteorologists and an electronics engineer were monitoring the radar during the sighting,The echo appeared to move 4 to 5 miles during successive radar sweeps,All observers believed that the refractive field was not caused by weather or other interference.
witness description: Two meteorologists and an electronics engineer
